abstract: The American Colonization Society is making preparations to start a vessel from Norfolk, Virginia, the first of May, with emigrants for Liberia. One hundred and seventy-eight persons have already applied for a passage; of whom one hundred and fourteen are from Virginia, fifty-two from North Carolina, six from Kentucky, three from Massachusotts, one from Ohio, one from Pennsylvania, and one from New-York.

abstract: ASSAILING A DEAD MAN.--Mr. COGGSWELL says: "It is to me matter of deep regret that we cannot have the advice of woman in our legislative deliberations--especially on a subject in which she is so deeply interested (temperance.) abstract: President FILLMORE gives an elegant entertainment to-morrow to the President-elect. Messrs.
